cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  This software is an unofficial replication study of the GenDFIR paper.
  When citing this software, please ALSO cite the original paper.
title: "yushin-gendfir-rag"
authors:
  - family-names: "Bang"
    given-names: "Juwon"
    alias: "YuShin"
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/Juwon1405/yushin-gendfir-rag"
abstract: >-
  An unofficial Python re-implementation of the GenDFIR pipeline
  (Loumachi, Ghanem & Ferrag, 2024). Provides a modular RAG + LLM
  pipeline (chunking, embedding, top-k retrieval, scaled-dot-product
  attention, timeline generation) for cyber-incident timeline analysis,
  along with synthetic test scenarios and unit tests covering the
  paper's core equations.
keywords:
  - DFIR
  - Digital Forensics
  - Incident Response
  - RAG
  - Retrieval-Augmented Generation
  - Large Language Models
  - Llama
  - Timeline Analysis
references:
  - type: article
    title: "GenDFIR: Advancing Cyber Incident Timeline Analysis Through Retrieval-Augmented Generation and Large Language Models"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Loumachi"
        given-names: "Fatma Yasmine"
      - family-names: "Ghanem"
        given-names: "Mohamed Chahine"
      - family-names: "Ferrag"
        given-names: "Mohamed Amine"
    year: 2024
    url: "https://github.com/GenDFIR"
    notes: >-
      Cyber Security Research Centre, London Metropolitan University, UK;
      Cybersecurity Institute, University of Liverpool, UK.
